LES MILLS+ PRIVACY POLICY
LAST UPDATED: 11 March 2024
Les Mills Media Limited (“LMM”, “us”, “our” or “we”), a company incorporated in New Zealand with its address at 200 Victoria Street West, Auckland 1010, New Zealand, operates the lesmillsondemand.com website (including all content and functionality available through the lesmillsondemand.com domain name and any country or region-specific domains or sub domains) and the LES MILLS+ App (jointly referred to as the “site”).
LMM is committed to ensuring the privacy and protection of information users provide to us. The following privacy policy governs LMM’s practices for information collection, use, processing, disclosure, transfer and retention on the site. This policy should be read with any other policy or terms developed by LMM from time to time and notified on the site or any part of the site (including the LES MILLS+ Terms of Use if you are a subscriber).
This policy may change from time to time and, if it does, the latest version will be available on our site or our app (and, where appropriate, brought to your attention).
Key points:
Les Mills Media Limited is the data controller of personal information processed through your use of our site.
The type of the personal information processed by us includes information that you provide when using our site or services, technical      information about your device, settings and site use, information that we receive from third parties, such as other website providers, ad networks, social media companies and health and fitness clubs and, where applicable, information relating to your role as instructor.
We use your data, amongst other things, to provide you with our site and services or information about them, tailor our services to you, analyse our services, provide (or allow others to provide) targeted ads, comply with any legal or regulatory obligation and (if you are an instructor) assess your performance and provide information relating to your role.
You agree that, to the extent permitted under applicable law, we may send you marketing materials relating to our services which you can opt out of at any time by sending an email to privacy@lesmills.com or clicking unsubscribe at the bottom of any marketing email.
We share data with our service providers and other third parties for the performance of our contractual obligations to you, to provide you with information, for the serving of advertising and (where relevant) run credit and background checks.
Depending on where you are located, you have a number of rights that you may exercise in relation to our use of your personal data, and      you may exercise these by emailing your request to
privacy@lesmills.com
.
You can find information about us and how we collect, use and store your personal data in each section of this policy.
